values
('computer-science:2-5-2-the-integrated-development-environment-ide:tips:56ae7cb2', 'computer-science', 'computer-science:2-5-2-the-integrated-development-environment-ide', '2.5.2 The Integrated Development Environment (IDE)', 'tips', 'mcq', 1, '{"readingTitle": "tip — Naming the IDE tool, not just describing it", "reading": "<p>Many marks are lost by describing what a tool does without naming it, or vice versa. If a question asks to <strong>identify</strong> a tool, give the <strong>name</strong> (e.g. \"a breakpoint\"). If it asks to <strong>explain</strong> or <strong>describe</strong>, give the name <strong>and</strong> say what it does.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Learn the tools in pairs — name + what it does: syntax highlighting → colours the code; breakpoint → pauses the program; watching variables → shows a variable''s value.</li>\n</ul>", "question": "A question asks you to ''identify'' the IDE tool that pauses a program at a chosen line.", "options": ["Describe in detail how the whole of the IDE works, from start to finish", "Name the tool: a breakpoint", "List every debugging tool the IDE provides, one after another", "Explain why syntax errors are different from logic errors"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 1, "explain": "''Identify'' asks for the name of the tool — a breakpoint. A full description is only needed if the question says ''explain'' or ''describe''."}'::jsonb),
('computer-science:2-5-2-the-integrated-development-environment-ide:tips:ef25fb73', 'computer-science', 'computer-science:2-5-2-the-integrated-development-environment-ide', '2.5.2 The Integrated Development Environment (IDE)', 'tips', 'mcq', 1, '{"readingTitle": "explain — Editing tools vs debugging tools — know which is which", "reading": "<p>Questions often ask you to sort IDE facilities into groups. Keep two groups clear in your head:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Helps you write code</strong>: syntax highlighting, auto-indentation, auto-complete.</li>\n<li><strong>Helps you find and fix errors</strong>: syntax error flagging, breakpoints, stepping, watching variables.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>The run-time environment and the translator sit slightly apart — they let the code be <strong>tested</strong> and <strong>run</strong> from inside the IDE.</p>", "question": "Which of these belongs in the group ''helps a programmer find and fix errors''?", "options": ["Auto-complete, because it inserts a suggested name for the programmer automatically", "Watching variables", "Auto-indentation, because it lines new code up to match the block it is inside", "Syntax highlighting, because it colours the code to make it easier to read"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 1, "explain": "Watching variables is a debugging tool used to find errors. Auto-complete, auto-indentation and syntax highlighting all help with writing code."}'::jsonb),
('computer-science:2-5-2-the-integrated-development-environment-ide:tips:e0d2983b', 'computer-science', 'computer-science:2-5-2-the-integrated-development-environment-ide', '2.5.2 The Integrated Development Environment (IDE)', 'tips', 'mcq', 1, '{"readingTitle": "tip — Explain HOW a tool helps, not just WHAT it is", "reading": "<p>A common exam pattern is: \"State a tool an IDE provides, and explain how it helps a programmer.\" Two marks usually need <strong>two separate ideas</strong> — naming the tool is not enough on its own for full marks.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Weak:</strong> \"Breakpoints\" (name only).</li>\n<li><strong>Better:</strong> \"A breakpoint pauses the program at a chosen line, so the programmer can examine what is happening at that point rather than guessing.\"</li>\n</ul>", "question": "A question is worth 2 marks and asks you to ''state a debugging tool and explain how it helps''. What should your answer include?", "options": ["Just the name of the tool, written as clearly and neatly as possible", "The name of the tool AND an explanation of how it helps the programmer", "A full list of every debugging tool the IDE provides, without any explanation", "A diagram of the IDE''s editor window, with no written explanation at all"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 1, "explain": "A 2-mark ''state and explain'' question needs both the name of the tool and an explanation of how it helps — not just one or the other."}'::jsonb),
